definition.value: A p-coumaroylagmatine in which the double bond of the coumaroyl component has Z-geochemistry.
A N-octadecenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is (11Z)-octadecenoyl.
An oxysterol that is cholesterol which is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4beta and 24S.
A  phosphatidylcholine 30:0 in which the acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 is pentadecanoyl.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:0 in which the acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and myristoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:0 in which the acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 are myristoyl and stearoyl respectively.
A member of the class of cinnamamides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-hydroxy-3-methoxycinnamid with the amino group of agmatine.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are oleoyl and myristoyl respectively.
A 4-hydroxy-3-methoxycinnamoylagmatine in which the double bond of the 4-hydroxy-3-methoxycinnamoyl component has Z-geochemistry.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:3 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.
A 3beta-hydroxycholest-5-en-26-al in which the stereocentre at position 25 has R-configuration.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl respectively.
A 3beta-hydroxycholest-5-en-26-oate in which the stereocentre at position 25 has R-configuration.
A  phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl respectively.

A phosphatidylcholine 34:4 in which teh acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

A fatty-acyl group derived from (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoic acid.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoic acid.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:0 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are tetradecanoyl and docosanoyl respectively.
An N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl group derived from N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)-[N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine.
A 1-octadecanoyl-2-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (11Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (6Z)-hexadecenoyl.
A 1-octadecanoyl-2-octadecenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (11Z)-octadecenoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.
An oxysterol that is cholesterol which is substituted by hydroxy groups at 4beta and 26 positions and has R-configuration at position 25.
A 1,2-di-octadecenoylsn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 is 11Z)-octadecenoyl .
A 26-oxo steroid resulting from the oxidation of the terminal methyl group of 4beta,26-dihydroxycholesterol to the corresponding aldehyde.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25R)-3beta,4beta-dihydroxycholest-5-en-26-oic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:3 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (8E,10E,12Z)-octadecatrienoic acid
A phosphatidylcholine 36:3 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecanoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.
A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (11Z)-hexadec-11-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:3 in which the acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatrienoyl respectively.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (10E,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A  phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

A member of the class of azobenzenes that is azobenzene in which one of the phenyl groups is substituted at the para position by a sulfo group, while the other is substituted at a meta position by a sulfo group and at the para position by an amino group. The disodium salt is the biological stain 'fast yellow'.
An organosulfonate oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the sulfo groups of 4-aminoazobenzene-3,4'-disulfonic acid.

An organic sodium salt that is 4-aminoazobenzene-3,4'-disulfonic acid in which the protons of both of the sulfo groups have been replaced by sodium ions. It is used as a biological stain. It was formerly used as a food coloring agent (E105), but its use in food or drinks is now forbidden.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.
An L-tryptophan derivative in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the indole ring is replaced by a methyl group.

A tryptamine alkaloid that is N,N-dimethyltryptamine carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 4. A hallucinogenic alkaloid isolated in trace amounts from Psilocybe mushrooms (also known as Teonanacatl or "magic mushrooms").
A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.
A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholestane-3beta-ol having double bonds at the 8,9- and 14,15- positions.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (9Z,12Z)-hexadeca-9,12,15-trienoic acid.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:4  in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-octadecenoyl and (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatetraenoyl respectively.
